procstep.procdesc: Unioned together all input layers and attributed a common field, then dissolved on that common field. Order of presidence was forest ownership, then ODF, then DNR, then BLM and last was rural fire disticts.
Dataset copied to R6 Fire Template Fire Planning Data Set. Added 3 Required Feature Level Metadata Fields and populated where possible. Updated Metadata

Unioned together all input layers and attributed a common field, then dissolved on that common field. Order of presidence was forest ownership, then ODF, then DNR, then BLM and last was rural fire disticts.This operation was for area to the East and South East of the PICC Dispatch area. By doing this area we finished the NOIDC dispatch area. We also added some more domains to the geodb and updated the metadata

updated the location of the East Umatilla RFD, Heppner City RFD, ODF and DNR Protection Responsibility. DNRand ODF Boundaries locations were downloaded from the Respective State GISWeb sites. Heppner and Umatilla RFD locations were provided by Brian Goff for this update. Also the protection agency domain was changed to allow duel protection by both a RFD and ODF or DNR
